    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Technique of blowing for the purpose of coloring or decorating. An example is in decorating porcelain, where powdered pigment is blown through a hollow tube, passing through a piece of gauze attached at the other end to ensure that the pigment spreads evenly.</Note_Text>
